"'One child--one dear little romper just six years old. Oh, if you could see him killing cockroaches
with a slipper! Smack! smack! smack! Three gone before you could wink!' He leaned back in his chair
and laughed his eyes into his head again.

"I was a little startled at the nature of the child's amusement, but the father's laughter made me
think that perhaps he was joking.

"'My sole duties, then,' I asked, 'are to take charge of a single child?'